This paper presents a new knowledge graph, EventKG, that focuses on events and temporal relations. Therefore, it is likely to be relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for its use of natural language processing techniques, computational linguistics (cs.CL) for its focus on multilingual information, information retrieval (cs.IR) for its use in semantic analytics, databases (cs.DB) for its use of knowledge graphs, and machine learning (cs.LG) for its use of canonical representations.
